The Vice President and Secretary Blinken spoke at the U.S. Department of State Headquarters to thank the staff for their dedication and service. They emphasized the importance of upholding democracy, human rights, and the rule of law. They also highlighted the connection between domestic and foreign policies and the impact they have on everyday Americans. The Vice President expressed the need to reinforce democracy, combat the pandemic, rebuild the economy, address racial injustice, and tackle climate change. They emphasized that America must show its commitment to delivering on these issues to both allies and adversaries.